what you'll find most likely

00:04:27.490 --> 00:04:33.720
is that you've got a bunch
of tasks that are done.

00:04:33.720 --> 00:04:39.130
You have an undone task, a
bunch of tasks that are done,

00:04:39.130 --> 00:04:43.450
an undone task, and then some
stuff done, and a whole bunch

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:44.560
of undone tasks.

00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:47.200
And the game's only this done.

00:04:47.200 --> 00:04:48.780
You are not here.

00:04:48.780 --> 00:04:49.610
You are not here.

00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:51.520
You are here.

00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:54.220
And you need to be able
to see that as a team.

00:04:54.220 --> 00:04:56.250
You need to be able
to actually see,

00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:59.710
what is the highest, most
important thing that's

00:04:59.710 --> 00:05:01.580
still not completed?

00:05:01.580 --> 00:05:03.530
Right now, at the
level of granularity

00:05:03.530 --> 00:05:05.980
that we're looking at all
of your product backlogs,

00:05:05.980 --> 00:05:08.490
all of your product
backlogs don't quite

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:10.090
